<div class="yui-content">
<div id="wiki-tab-0-0">
<div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:100%;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/fragment:5000contestfourminorsix-2/slide1.png" style="width:100%;" alt="slide1.png" class="image" />
<div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:100%;">
<p>Slide 1 of 12</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>(Distribute supplementary document to Ms. Raj/classmates before starting)</p>
<p><strong>SILAS:</strong> Good morning Ms. Raj and fellow classmates, he's Paul -</p>
<p><strong>PAUL:</strong> - and I'm Paul -</p>
<p><strong>SILAS:</strong> and we'll now be presenting our literature coursework on our chosen prompt, namely, <em>A Literary Frankenstein!</em> That's right, today we're donning the lab coats so you lovely people can watch us disassemble, analyse, and bastardise -</p>
<p><strong>PAUL:</strong> <em>(sternly)</em> Synthesise.</p>
<p><strong>SILAS:</strong> Yes - <em>synthesise</em> - two completely unrelated fictional works! Namely, Richard Adams' fantasy rabbit adventure Watership Down…</p>
<p><strong>PAUL:</strong> …and the online collaborative fiction platform, <em>The SCP Foundation</em>! Which makes the coats somewhat topical, as you'll see later.</p>
<p><strong>SILAS:</strong> <em>(giving an approving shoulder-smack)</em> Touché, <em>Theophilus</em>, didn't even realise. But anyway! Why this diabolical experiment? What might be accomplished through such galling malpractice?</p>
<p><strong>PAUL:</strong> Well, simple. We want to use everybody's favourite rabbits to induct you all to the miracle that is collaborative fiction. Ah, writing stuff together: a simple idea with endless artistic potential and the ability to, well, save your life.</p>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-1" style="display:none">
<div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:100%;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/fragment:5000contestfourminorsix-2/slide2.png" style="width:100%;" alt="slide2.png" class="image" />
<div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:100%;">
<p>Slide 2 of 12</p>
</div>
</div>
<p><strong>SILAS:</strong> Hazel and his fellow rabbits have just finished digging their brand-new warren, the Honeycomb. But don't be deceived: there's nothing sweet about their situation, and the atmosphere is fraught with worry. The Owsla, the head honchos, are having a frantic gathering in the central chamber. And by that I mean everyone, because they're all family to Hazel. Good guy Hazel!</p>
<p><strong>PAUL:</strong> Trouble is, these rabbits have seen a terrible thing on their travels, and nobody can agree what they've been through. They're all just yapping over one another. Where's this warren and why is it so nasty? Does it have a literal roof of bones? Hold on, who's this shady Cowslip figure? What on earth is a scut?</p>
<p><strong>SILAS:</strong> It's a rabbit's tail.</p>
<p><strong>PAUL:</strong> Oh.</p>
</div>
<div id="wiki-tab-0-2" style="display:none">
<div class="scp-image-block block-right" style="width:100%;"><img src="http://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/fragment:5000contestfourminorsix-2/slide3.png" style="width:100%;" alt="slide3.png" class="image" />
<div class="scp-image-caption" style="width:100%;">
<p>Slide 3 of 12</p>
</div>
</div>
<p>(Both don bunny ears.)</p>
<p><strong>SILAS, as DANDELION:</strong> <em>(breathlessly, miming impassioned argument)</em> yeah but you see clearly Cowslip deserves to die they have grown fat and languid why you no listen to me I'm totally not going back there it was bigger than a breadbox</p>
<p><strong>PAUL, as HAZEL:</strong> <em>(pointing accusingly)</em> OBJECTION!</p>
<p>(Dandelion hangs his head contritely, with an exaggerated ear-flop.)</p>
<p><strong>HAZEL:</strong> Good Frith, surely nothing will come from this swollen morass of half-truths! We shall sooner expire from your squabbling than from the creatures of the field. Could we all take a moment to compose ourselves?</p>
<p>(Silence.)</p>
<p><strong>HAZEL:</strong> Dandelion!</p>
<p><strong>DANDELION:</strong> <em>(with servility soon tempered by concern)</em>: Oh! Me! &#8230;Yes, Hazel?</p>
<p><strong>HAZEL:</strong> Dandelion, you have always been an eloquent and faithful chronicler. Clearly, we have met an unspeakable evil, and woe befall us if we fail to set the record straight. So have I prepared you an <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/how-to-write-an-scp">assignment</a>, that we might reckon with our frightful encounter. Our race is cunning and full of tricks; we ought to know and confront our devourers.</p>
<p><strong>DANDELION:</strong> Wow Hazel, that's deep.</p>
<p>(Silence.)</p>
<p><strong>DANDELION:</strong> Aye aye.</p>
<p>(Silas mimes the process of writing, seemingly engrossed in some creative endeavour. Paul removes the bunny ears.)</p>
<p><strong>PAUL:</strong> What exactly did Hazel ask Dandelion to do? Well, whatever it is, we can be sure of one thing -</p>
<p>(Silas reaches under the presenters' desk, producing a piece of paper signifying the completed work.)</p>
<p><strong>PAUL and SILAS (in unison):</strong> Precise description saves lives.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
